  "dct_description_sm": [
    "U.S. Large Area Landmarks represents common landmark areas in the United States.The landmark area types (and examples or definitions of what may exist within each type) are military territories (installations, barracks, practice grounds, and roads), hospitals (buildings, roads, parking, and green areas), educational institutions (buildings, roads, parking, and green areas), shopping centers (buildings with individual shops, parking, and related facilities), industrial areas (artificial cover with buildings), amusement parks (areas for public entertainment with buildings, green areas, related facilities, and parking), stadiums (athletic or sports grounds with tiers of seats for spectators and parking), golf courses (areas used to play golf and facilities such as buildings and parking), and cemeteries (areas dedicated for the interment of human remains)."
